{
  "schema": 1,
  "comment": "The toolkit's shipped artifact set. tools/refresh.py reconciles a governed repo to exactly this set. Classes: replace-whole (byte-exact copy of the template, replaced only when the existing file matches a current or formerly-shipped template version - anything else is flagged, never overwritten); replace-if-unmodified (missing = install; matches a formerly-shipped version = update to current; anything else = owner-modified, flagged, never overwritten); retired (formerly-shipped target paths removed only when they match a formerly-shipped version, otherwise flagged). All matching is newline-equivalent sha256: CRLF -> LF, and content differing only by at most one trailing final newline matches (issue #1). formerly[] lists normalized hashes of every version ever shipped, from git history. MAINTENANCE RULE: whenever a shipped source file changes, append the OUTGOING version's normalized hash to its formerly[] in the same commit - otherwise deployed copies of that version get flagged owner-modified instead of updated.",
